The '''Mississippi Beach Kings''' were an [[indoor soccer]] team based in [[Biloxi, Mississippi|Biloxi]], [[Mississippi]].  They played their games in the [[Mississippi Coast Coliseum]]. They were members of the [[Eastern Indoor Soccer League]] and played only during the 1998 season. During the 1997 season, the team played in [[Columbus, Georgia|Columbus]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] as the '''Columbus Comets'''.<ref name=season>[http://www.sover.net/~spectrum/eisl.html EISL page on USA Soccer Archives]</ref> During their existence, the Beach Kings/Comets played a total of 52 games, winning 23, two via shootout, and losing 35, four via shootout. They scored a total of 595 goals and allowed a total of 719 goals and notched 65 total points in standings out of a possible 156 points.<ref name=season>[http://www.sover.net/~spectrum/eisl.html EISL page on USA Soccer Archives]</ref> 

==History==
===1997 season===
The '''Columbus Comets''' finished 7th overall in the 7 team league. They finished with a record of 3 wins, 21 losses and 3 shootout losses for 12 points.<ref name=season>[http://www.sover.net/~spectrum/eisl.html EISL page on USA Soccer Archives]</ref>

===1998 season===
The '''Mississippi Beach Kings''' finished 2nd overall in the 7 team league. They finished the season with a record of 18 wins, 10 losses, 2 shootout wins and 1 shootout loss for 53 points. The Beach Kings made the playoffs, defeating the [[Huntsville Fire]] 2 games to 1 in the semi-final round. In the championship game, the Beach Kings lost to the [[Lafayette SwampCats]] 10-9.<ref name=season>[http://www.sover.net/~spectrum/eisl.html EISL page on USA Soccer Archives]</ref>

